# No goto

Do not use `goto` in this project. Use structured control flow instead:

- **Loop exit**: Use `break` to exit loops
- **Early return**: Use `return` or `break` to exit early
- **Cleanup**: Use RAII, or place cleanup code after the loop so it runs on both normal exit and `break`

```cpp
// ❌ BAD
while (running) {
  if (read(fd, buf, size) <= 0) goto done;
  process(buf);
}
done:
flush();
cleanup();

// ✅ GOOD
while (running) {
  if (read(fd, buf, size) <= 0) break;
  process(buf);
}
flush();
cleanup();
```
